(thirdQuint)A Randomized Controlled Trial Evaluating the Effectiveness of a Salvia-based Mouthwash in Palliative Care.

 The aim of this study is to examine the effectiveness of an herbal mouthwash made from salvia officinalis (SO) in maintaining good oral health among patients in palliative care.

 The study compares a mouthwash based on salvia tea solution with conventional normal saline mouthwash and addresses the following research questions: 1.

 Does the SO-based mouthwash provide a better treatment than conventional normal saline in maintaining good oral health in terminally ill patients? 2.

 Is there a difference in the individual perception of oral comfort in patients receiving SO versus patients receiving saline rinsing solution?.

